comments.body:
In alma, the holding has no items. It's upsetting that Alma provides the same message for a holding with no items as it does for when some items are unavailable.

In my opinion, this would be treated as an In Process request from the request form, but I'd want Circulation to weigh in on that.

We have treated holdings with no items like this as exceptions for years that go to recap problems. I don't think we really should change anything here. We cannot truly say what the item's status until someone goes and looks for it.

Looking at the form on staging it's working well. The only UX concern I'd have is the amount of text displayed before the form. I wonder if the committee might consider shortening it.
The group IRMWG will review the form. This should not block the PR.

Kevin has a meeting with the vendor on 2/9/2023 and will discuss implementation then. 

Possible concerns:
- Button is slow to display on the page
- Text of the button does not match current implementation ("Where to find it" vs. "Map it")
Deploy to catalog-qa and demo to the vendor tomorrow 02/09/2023.

@kevinreiss  - We also have a failing accessibility test - the map icon is not aria-hidden, which I think is a change they need to make on the vendor side. See https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/pull/3402/files#diff-6a0e1ff4df89c6ea88feb537aba63ebace11bdf033243f820206d9e736febebf
